<br>
Bolt spells do more damage than our DD's. There's times when you will want to use DD's over bolts though.<br>
<br>
- All our bolts are fire based, if the mob is highy fire resistant, landing bolts on them is a futile waste of mana<br>
<br>
- In a group, your group members can block shots which wastes mana. Usually easier to use DD's if your in a group.<br>
<br>
- Except for Scars of Sigil, our DD's cast faster than bolts<br>
<br>
- Also in a group, or raid, if mobs are getting pushed into walls (even partially), bolts will fail. The whole model has to be showing, if part of it is in a wall or ceiling, the bolt is blocked.<br>
<br>
- Bolts are projectiles, they will hit anything between you and your target (but only the first thing hit actually takes damage). Usually not an issue, but if your fighting from long range and have alot of roamers, you might wind up hitting the wrong mob.<br>
<br>
Other than that, they're good spells IMO. Good mana:damage ratios, and fairly high damage output. Plus newbies are pretty impressed when they see bolts flying off into space from the other side of the zone =). Oh, a tip to using them in groups. Stand right next to the mob, in melee range and then cast. Usually gets rid of alot of the blocking issues.<br>
